<br>
Group environment is VERY different.  This is what really gets Necros into trouble.  They're so solo oriented that most players never learn how to work in a group environment and suck at the endgame.  Your method of playing wasn't wrong (except for breaking mezzes).. it just wasn't right for a group.<br>
<br>
ALWAYS find out your job when you join the group.  Will you be buffer, main healer, backup healer, DOTs, crowd control, etc?  <br>
<br>
If there are two of you (same class) split the jobs and make sure you aren't casting the same spells. (I cast venom of snake on Mob_01.  Then you cast VoS on Mob_01.  We have both wasted the mana for the spell.. but the mob only has ONE Venom of Snake spell draining its life.)  IMPORTANT:  this is only for debuffers and DOTs.  DD's (direct damage spells) do their damage instantly so feel free to use the same nukes (DD's) as other people.<br>
<br>
To the rest of us, we were ALL new once and had no clue what in the hell our class was for.. lol.. well.. maybe the meatshields (but we love you anyways).  If someone in your group is obviously not with the program... try taking a second to educate them.  Maybe they are not just sucking exp.. but honestly know no better.  Because we are playing an alt for kicks doesn't mean everyone is.<br>
